    "content": "On the next few pages, your students will engage with real data from sources like NASA and the US Geological Survey. These data can be messy, and that's okay!\n\nFrom this point until the end of the module, the goal is to support students' ongoing changes in thinking. *This is a great place to stop the class and elicit students' ideas.* What are their initial ideas? \n\nLearn more about  <a href=\"https://ambitiousscienceteaching.org/planning-engagement-important-science-ideas-3/\" target=\"_blank\">supporting students' changes in ongoing thinking</a>. ",
