{
  "tipType": "questionWrapper",
  "questionWrapper": {
    "correctExplanation": "GPS data show Africa moving northeast. In the past, this means that Africa must have been southwest of where it is now.",
    "distractorsExplanation": "If students say that Africa was northeast of where it is now, ask them to describe the current movement from the GPS data. Students should say that Africa is moving northeast now. How can Africa have been farther in the direction that it's currently moving?\n\nIf students say that Africa was in about the same position 10 million years ago, ask them to focus on the GPS data. Is Africa moving today? Why would it have just started moving now and not have been moving for the past 10 million years?",
    "exemplar": "",
    "teacherTip": "If the students have incorrectly answered this question, check their explanations in the next question to see why. \n\nYou may need to review the meanings of the green circles and yellow lines in the map. It may also be helpful to make sure students know where Africa is on the map.",
    "teacherTipImageOverlay": ""
  },
