  "windowShade": {
    "windowShadeType": "theoryAndBackground",
    "layout": "mediaLeft",
    "content": "**Seismic Explorer** (SE) is designed to support the visualization of real-world, real-time data about earthquakes, volcanoes, and plate motion. Students use SE to (1) look for patterns in earthquakes across Earth's surface, (2) examine the relationships between earthquakes, volcanoes, and landform distributions, and (3) zoom into cross-sections of Earth to investigate earthquake depth patterns to understand plate dynamics. \n\nThroughout the module, students use data gathered from explorations of SE and from investigations of geographic profiles to develop hypotheses about the nature of the dynamics of the plate system on Earth. ",
    "content2": "",
    "mediaType": "none",
    "mediaCaption": "Last, First. \"Title of Work.\" Year created. Site Title [OR] Publisher. Gallery [OR] Location. http://www.url.com.",
