    "teacherTip": "Students may consider the ideas related to earthquakes occurring where pieces of Earth come together. Some may state that earthquakes and volcanoes occur where gaps or spaces occur between pieces. \n\nAt this point in the module, do not  persuade or dissuade students of their ideas; rather, the goal is to get students to hypothesize and share their ideas. \n\nSee this document for a list of some common ideas that students may have at this point in the <a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1owbTKdQOY3LPsvd2a7ot2EegSy0ne5DAaw1ozE6TpjA/edit?usp=sharing\" target=\"_blank\">Plate Tectonics Learning Progression</a>.\n",
