  "windowShade": {
    "windowShadeType": "theoryAndBackground",
    "layout": "mediaLeft",
    "content": "Students will be comparing this oceanic-oceanic convergent boundary (the Aleutians) to the continental-oceanic convergent boundary they just explored (the Andes). \n\nThere are many similar features including an ocean trench, volcanoes appearing in a line on the overriding plate, and a pattern of descending earthquakes. By exploring a convergent boundary with different features, students can look for commonalities across the two.  \n\nAfter students complete this case, it is important to have a whole class discussion. Discussion questions are at the bottom of this page. \n",
