    "content": "This final case, exploring the formation of the Himalayan Mountains, allows students to explore a continental-continental crust collision. \n\nBy the end of this case it is important to make sure students are thinking about the following: \n\n * When continental crust approaches a convergent boundary it will **NOT** subduct. It doesn’t matter if there is another continent on the other side or not.\n\n * In order for two continents to collide along a boundary, an ocean **must** disappear first. \n\nThis occurs because oceanic crust subducts below continental crust. ",
