    "correctExplanation": "",
    "distractorsExplanation": "",
    "exemplar": "The plate that India is on contains parts that are both ocean and continent. Before India reached Asia, ocean had to disappear. \n\nThe ocean part of the plate went underneath the Asia plate. As the ocean part went underneath, the amount of ocean decreased until India finally collided with Asia.\n\n On the surface, mountains were formed as the plates came together.",
   "teacherTip": "Help students differentiate between the ocean part of a plate (that is, land that is underwater) vs. ocean, which is what we call the water on top of the oceanic part of the plate. \n\nThis is complicated, but it is important for avoiding confusion between closing ocean and \"disappearing\" plate.\n\nOne common point of confusion for students is the difference between \"ocean\" and \"oceanic plate material\" or \"oceanic crust\". By not differentiating between the two, students often think it is the ocean water that is subducting. \n\nThough some water does get into the mantle this way, it is not where the ocean water goes as oceans close due to converging plates.",
