{
  "tipType": "questionWrapper",
  "questionWrapper": {
    "correctExplanation": "",
    "distractorsExplanation": " ",
    "exemplar": "Fifty million years ago, the ocean part of the Indian plate was going under Asia (just like the ocean plate going under the Andes mountain range today), so there would have been deepening earthquakes along the place where the two pieces meet. The earthquakes would have been shallow at the edge of the boundary and deeper farther inland.\n\nIn the past 50 million years, all of the ocean crust has gone under Asia and the continental crust from India has met up with the continental crust from Asia. \n\nThe continental crusts do not go under one another. This has caused the Himalayas to form as India and Asia have collided and pushed up at their continental edges.",
