  "windowShade": {
    "windowShadeType": "discussionPoints",
    "layout": "mediaLeft",
    "content": "This is a good time to talk with the students about their ideas and transfer some of the ideas to the Summary Table. Some questions to guide this discussion:\n\n* What are some of the ways that we now know plates interact with one another?\n\n* How do these interactions shape the surface of Earth?\n* How does understanding how plates come together help us to predict what Earth might look like in 500 million years?\n\nYou can also check their understanding through the Teacher Dashboard. This is especially helpful for students who may not be vocal in class discussions. ",
    "content2": "",
    "mediaType": "none",
