  "windowShade": {
    "windowShadeType": "theoryAndBackground",
    "layout": "mediaLeft",
    "content": "The goal of this activity is to have students consider the idea that **each of Earth’s tectonic plates is surrounded by adjacent plates and interacts, as it moves, with those plates along all these shared boundaries.** \n\nThis systems view is more complex but gives students a less disjointed notion of plate tectonics. Typically, students learn about convergent, divergent, and transform boundaries independently and rarely consider how the movements are all connected.\n\nThis activity begins by having students consider what must be happening on one side of a plate if the other side of the plate has a convergent boundary. Students investigate divergence, learn about transform boundaries, and think about multiple plate interactions. \n\n",
    "content2": "",
    "mediaType": "none",
