    "distractorsExplanation": "The plates are not moving towards each other. The evidence that supports this is that the pattern is not the same as the Andes and the Aleutians, where plates are moving towards each other.\n\nAlso, the earthquake cross-section does not show that earthquakes are getting deeper, which means that a plate cannot be going underneath another. The geographic profile does not show a trench that would indicate a plate moving underneath another.\n\nThe plates must be moving relative to each other if there are earthquakes and volcanoes. If the plates were not moving, then there shouldn't be any earthquakes or volcanoes.\n\n",
