    "windowShadeType": "diggingDeeper",
    "layout": "mediaLeft",
    "content": "**In Earth's history, the continents have moved together and broken apart several times.**\n\nAsk students: how do you think Earth's continents moved together and then broke apart?\nWhat plate interactions had to happen to bring the continents together?\nWhat plate interactions had to happen to break up the continents?\n\n_In Earth's history, the continents have come together and broken apart several times._\n\n_To come together, there had to be convergent boundaries. The plates with the continents had to move towards each other. Any ocean that was between continents would have been subducted (like how India moved up to collide with Asia) and mountains formed._\n\n_Meanwhile, on the other side of the planet, somewhere there had to be divergence, plates moving apart. These parts had to be all ocean to be able to get the continents to be all smashed together._\n\n_Once the continents were all together, you could still tell the plate boundaries. These would be marked by mountain ranges as the edges of the continents collided and were unable to subduct._\n\n_At some point, the continents started to move apart. To get them to move apart, there had to be divergent boundaries. This would have split the supercontinent at its mountain ranges, the edges of the plates that came together._\n\n_The continents moved away from each other at these divergent boundaries, and once the land got low enough (after the mountains were pulled apart), oceans started to form between the continents. Eventually, this started to look like the modern mid-ocean ridges, with volcanoes at their centers._\n\n_Meanwhile, somewhere on the other side of the planet, there needed to be convergence. Since the continents were moving apart, the oceans had to be coming together. So the oceans got smaller as the continents moved apart. But as the continents continued to move apart, new oceans were created._",
    "content2": "",
    "mediaType": "none",
    "mediaCaption": "Last, First. \"Title of Work.\" Year created. Site Title [OR] Publisher. Gallery [OR] Location. http://www.url.com.",
    "mediaURL": ""
  }
}

