    "content": "To understand Earth as a dynamic system, students must understand the mechanism that drives the motion of the plates. The goal of this activity is to introduce students to the forces that are applied to Earth’s plates.\n\n**Begin the activity by eliciting students’ ideas on what might be occurring in the mantle to cause plates to move.**\n\nStudents will also consider how oceanic plate material being formed at divergent boundaries and being destroyed (recycled) at convergent boundaries is related to forces in the mantle.\n\nFinally, students are introduced to the concept of mantle convection as well as to more recent theories scientists have about the mechanisms driving plate motion.\n\n",
