    "teacherTip": "Consider projecting this model in front of the classroom as you discuss what the arrows at each **__i__** mean. \n\n* At divergent boundaries, there are two arrows. Each arrow shows **half** of the spreading rate on each side of the boundary. Each plate moves away from the boundary at the same velocity. \n\n* At convergent boundaries there is one arrow, which shows the rate of the plate subducting with respect to the plate that is overriding it. \n\n* Transform boundaries are shown with arrows showing the rate of one plate relative to the plate it slides past. The relative motion is split across the two sides of the boundary.",
