    "correctExplanation": "\n",
    "distractorsExplanation": "",
    "exemplar": "In 200 million years, if the Red Sea keeps diverging, I would expect to find a mid-ocean ridge. It should look very much like today's mid-Atlantic ridge.\n\nThe new ocean (Red Ocean) would be deepest on either side of its center ridge. The center ridge would have many volcanoes. This is because magma comes to the surface to create new plate material at the divergent boundary.\n\nThe earthquakes would continue to be shallow and centered along the mid-ocean ridge. There would be additional earthquakes along the transform boundaries that form along the ridge. This would give the appearance of a zig-zag pattern for the mid-ocean ridge. ",
